<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 14 at 8:45PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of
northeastern Roanoke, east central Craig, northwestern Bedford and
Botetourt Counties and the northeastern City of Roanoke through 915
PM EDT...
At 844 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Cloverdale to near Stewartsville to
Goodview. Movement was north at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Roanoke...
Vinton...
Bedford...
Buchanan...
Troutville...
Stewartsville...
and Montvale.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
